I am Gregorio Maya, a senior spatial data consultant currently based in Madrid, (Spain). I am passionate about discovering the cues that drive behaviour in the built environment. With an MSc in Space Syntax and an honours Degree in Architecture, over the last 9 years in industry (urban consultancy, workplace strategy, and tech development) I have leveraged technical skills of data science to inform desing and policy based on data analysis and visualization. More recently, I have been collaborating with open source projects with PySAL devs (Python Spatial Analysis Libraries).
Academic activities are also a complementary part of my professional development. I am a frequent (virtual) lecturer at Universidad de los Andes (COL) and I often collaborate with professors at UCA Carnterbury (UK) and Universidad Nacional del Litoral (ARG).
